        title: "Introduction: Building a Case File",
        content: "A case file is the comprehensive document — or more often, collection of documents — that contains everything you need to run your arguments in a debate round. It includes your constructive case, evidence, anticipated opponent arguments, responses, and strategic notes. At the Master level, your case file should be a living document that evolves with each tournament and research session.\n\nThink of a case file as a debater's playbook. A football team does not walk onto the field with only one play. They have an entire book of plays designed for different situations, opponents, and game conditions. Your case file serves the same purpose: it prepares you for every scenario you might encounter.\n\nBuilding an excellent case file is one of the highest-leverage activities in competitive debate. An hour spent organizing and refining your case file will save you many hours of scrambling during prep time and produce better performance in rounds.",
